History 


















					<img src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw==" srcset="/content/corporate/en_US/about-axalta/history/_jcr_content/parMainContent/layoutcontainer/parMainContentLayout/col12/parMainContent/mediateaser/youtubeimage.axFitIn.mediaTeaser_mobile_x1.png/1461079432067/150+cover+image.png" title="" alt="">
				






150th Anniversary Video












In 2016, Axalta celebrates 150 years in the coatings industry. From the inception of our business in 1866 to the manufacture of next generation environmentally compatible products demanded in the 21st century, we have continued to evolve. What has not changed is a tradition of quality, technology, innovation, and leadership that puts our customers first. 
Some of the many highlights in the 150 year history of our company:
1866 
 

Herberts, the original producer of Standox® paint products is founded

1880
 

Spies Hecker® coatings company founded

1900s
 

Permanent® colors-first breakthrough enamel technology 
Begin nitrocellulose lacquer manufacture

1920s
 

Duco® paints manufactured by DuPont in the U.S. and Permaloid® paints manufactured by Spies Hecker® in Germany are introduced as sprayable paints
First color paint for automobiles adds consumer appeal

1930s
 

Dulux® alkyd enamel coating provides more durable finishes
 First mixing-machine tinting system developed to improve quality

1940s
 

Sand-mills revolutionize pigment dispersion efficiencies Automobile OEM and Refinish coating systems diverge with use of OEM high temperature drying ovens
ColorMasterTM colorimeter commercialized improving refinish color match

1950s
 

Standox® paints launch premium line
Lucite®acrylic resin, first thermoplastic acrylic, introduced
First to develop L,a,b color equations that became part of the foundation of modern color science
Established first Latin America plant in Tlalneplanta, Mexico

1960s
 

Centari® acrylic enamel launched
Nap-Gard® fusion bonded epoxy powder coatings launched for pipelines

1970s
 

Imron® polyurethane enamel introduced and Alesta® decorative powder coatings  launched

1980s
 

Introduced first spectrophotometer instrument
First waterborne OEM coatings in North America
First insulation coating Polyamid-imide overcoat
Replacement of 2-component to 1-component Voltatex® Impregnating Resins provides optimized cycle times and easier handling

1990s
 

Cromax® waterborne Refinish basecoat introduced
 DuPont acquires Herberts coating businesses
First spectrophotometer instrument introduced in the market
 Introduced organic-inorganic hybrid Voltatex® Core Sheet Varnish for electrical  steel coating

2000 - 2012
 

Formulate super-high solids coatings for OEMs
VINdicator color tool improves Refinish color matching
Consolidate systems with Eco-Concept paint improves productivity and performance for light vehicle OEMs
Establish first Asia-Pacific plants in China and India
Introduce Imron® Elite finishes
Introduce 3rd generation waterborne Cromax® Pro Basecoat 
Launch Waterborne 3-Wet for light vehicle OEMs
Launch ChromaPremier® Pro system for high-volume customers 
Acquire Plus™ EFX spectrophotometer that obtains color and flake data to create a new level of accuracy in color matching

2013
 

On February 1 Axalta Coating Systems becomes an independent company with a new name and identity
Announce investment to construct a new facility dedicated to waterborne coating   production in Shanghai
Invest in new pilot reactor to at our Coating Technology Center in Wilmington, DE
Launch Cormax refinish coatings line in Brazil
Introduce Cromax as the name of one of Axalta’s three global flagship refinish brand families
Establish new corporate headquarters in Philadelphia
Establish new headquarters for the company’s North America region in Glen Mills, PA
Celebrate 50th anniversary of operations in Brazil
Introduce SpectraMaster™ 3-D virtual color design tool for light vehicle OEM and refinish customers
Begin the Axalta Distinguished Lecture Series at University of Pennsylvania
Launch Nap-Gard® High Tg 7-2555 for underground and sub-sea pipelines
Celebrate 60 years of color trend reporting
Announce new UK offices and Training Academy for customers 

2014
 

 Issue 2013 Color Popularity Report
Announce the Axalta Sustainable Technology Education Program in China
Broke ground to expand manufacturing capacity for waterborne coatings in Shanghai
Announce construction in Wuppertal, Germany to expand capacity to produce waterborne coatings
Introduce next generation Voltatex® electrical insulation products in China
Launch Cromax Pro® Waterborne Basecoat in India
Launch Nason® Industrial coatings in Australia


Robert McLaughlin, Senior Vice President and CFO of Airgas Inc., joins Axalta Board of Directors
Open new commercial offices for Spanish operations in Sant Cugat del Vallès near Barcelona, Spain 
Publish 2013 Sustainability Report
Expand powder coatings production in China with joint venture partner Huajia Chemical Co. Ltd
Andreas Kramvis, Vice Chairman of Honeywell Inc., joins Axalta Board of Directors
Announce investment in Tlalnepantla, Mexico, to expand resin production for transportation coatings
Broke ground in Wuppertal, Germany to expand waterborne coating production capacity 
Axalta wins Leading Automotive Brand award in China
Globalize reach of Abcite™ and Alesta® powder coatings
Rebrand all Axalta electrocoat products under unified AquaEC™ brand name
Launch Alesta® ZeroZinc powder products
Announce the renewal of strategic partnership with the Huajia division of the Yongjia Group under a new name, Axalta-Huajia Coatings
Celebrate 50 years of commercial powder coatings
Introduce Acquire Plus EFX™ Spectrophotometer in China
Broke ground on construction of customer training facility in northwest Houston
On November 12 Axalta becomes publicly traded NYSE: AXTA
Open a new product development center at its facility in Lionville, PA
Launch new generation Voltatex® C6 electrical steel varnish

2015
 

Launch Color Block blog for North America market
Sign joint venture in China with Shanghai Kinlita Chemical to supply coatings for commercial vehicles
Inaugurate a refurbished technology center for powder coatings operations in Mexico 
Announce expansion of global vehicle product portfolio for agricultural, construction and earthmoving equipment (ACE) market
Open waterborne coatings plant in Shanghai
Announce support for the Mother River Protection program in China and the China Youth Development Foundation
Expand customer training facilities in Japan for refinish technicians
Receive GM Supplier of the Year award
Receive Hyundai Excellence in Purchasing supplier award in Brazil
Open first Center for Coating Technology Training in collaboration with the                  
Automotive Workshop Owners Association in Buenos Aires
Axalta commences Secondary Offering
Launch Imron® Hydro and Imron® Elite in China
Introduce second series of Alesta® Global Color Collection powder coatings
Standox® celebrates 60-year anniversary
Open Thailand’s third Cromax® Color Center in Chiang Rai
Introduce Acquire Plus EFX™ digital spectrophotometer for body shops in Korea
Begin construction on Asia-Pacific Technology Center in Shanghai
Cromax® Pro wins Green Repair Innovative Product Award in China
Celebrate 50-year anniversary of Nap-Gard® Powder Coatings 
Announce expansion of powder supply capabilities in the Southern California region 
Introduce Ganicin™ zinc-rich, corrosion-resistant coating system for industrial applications
Commission waterborne manufacturing facility in Wuppertal, Germany
Acquire Metalak Benelux B.V., importer of Spies Hecker coatings in the Netherlands and Belgium
Axalta receives Volvo Cars Quality of Excellence Award in Germany 
Introduce ReplaShade™ custom color match program for powder customers in North America
Pledge five year support for Ducks Unlimited conservation programs in North America
Broke ground on Axalta Customer Experience Center on the campus of Hendrick  Motorsports in Concord, NC
Announce construction of Global Innovation Center at The Navy Yard in Philadelphia, PA
Announce investment in India to double capacity and build coatings development center

2016
 

Axalta celebrates 150 years in the coatings industry
Ajax operations center in Canada celebrates 60 years of operations
Axalta Awards First State Robotics Scholarship
Axalta North America Launches the Learning Campus in Canada
Axalta and Jeff Gordon launch AquaEC 6100 at the ECOAT16 Conference 
Cromax unveils renovated European training center in Belgium
Inaugurates expanded resin production facility in Tlalnepantla, Mexico
Open expanded European Technology Center in Wuppertal, Germany
Axalta enhances powder coating capabilities at Montbrison, France Facilities
Axalta Debuts Nap-Gard Enhancements at NACE Corrosion 2016
Axalta becomes primary sponsor of Dale Earnhardt Jr.’s digital platform
Become a Founding Partner of the Daytona International Speedway’s Motorsports Stadium
Acquire Dura Coat Products, manufacturer of coil coatings in North America
Acquire High Performance Coating, manufacturer of refinish coating products in Malaysia
Acquire rigid thermoplastics division of United Paint and Chemicals providing interior coating to light vehicle manufacturers
Acquired Geeraets in the Netherlands, distributor of Cromax products
Axalta becomes 100% owned by public investors
Axalta and Ducks Unlimited announce first project, solidifying multi-year relationship

 




















