Axalta Coating Systems Implements Titanium Dioxide Surcharge on Selected Products


Date : 07/21/2017 @ 8:00AM


Source : Business Wire


Stock : Axalta Coating Systems Ltd. (AXTA)


Quote :  32.29  0.0 (0.00%) @ 4:00AM


 








Axalta Coating Systems Implements Titanium Dioxide Surcharge on Selected ProductsTweet


Print


AXALTA COATING SYSTEMS LTD. (NYSE:AXTA)Historical Stock Chart
1 Month : From Jun 2017 to Jul 2017



      Due to continuing significant price increases in the cost of titanium 
      dioxide over the past six months, Axalta Coating Systems (NYSE: AXTA) 
      will impose a price surcharge for coating products that contain this 
      critical raw material.
    

      The surcharge will be applied to specific products sold in all regions 
      of the world and is independent from any pricing actions due to the 
      long-term rise in the cost of producing resins and other key components 
      of Axalta products. The titanium dioxide surcharge will take effect on 
      all orders received after August 1, 2017.
    

About Axalta Coating Systems


      Axalta is a leading global company focused solely on coatings and 
      providing customers with innovative, colorful, beautiful and sustainable 
      solutions. From light OEM vehicles, commercial vehicles and refinish 
      applications to electric motors, buildings and pipelines, our coatings 
      are designed to prevent corrosion, increase productivity and enable the 
      materials we coat to last longer. With 150 years of experience in the 
      coatings industry, the over 13,000 people of Axalta continue to find 
      ways to serve our more than 100,000 customers in 130 countries better 
      every day with the finest coatings, application systems and technology. 
      For more information visit axalta.com 
      and follow us @Axalta on Twitter 
      and on LinkedIn.
    


View source version on businesswire.com: http://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20170721005066/en/
