Axalta Coating Systems Ltd. (NYSE:AXTA) Experiences Lighter than Usual Trading Volume - Highlight Press

























































Highlight PressBreaking Tech News, Entertainment, Mortgages and More
Axalta Coating Systems Ltd. (NYSE:AXTA) Experiences Lighter than Usual Trading Volume
July 24, 2017 By Clarence Martin Tweet        Advertisement





Trading volume for Axalta Coating Systems Ltd. was 76K on Tuesday.  Shares saw a steep decrease in trading volume of 95.83% under the normal average daily volume. 
 Axalta Coating Systems Ltd. (NYSE:AXTA) has been the object of insider selling activity recently.   Sean M. Lannon, VP Corp Fin & Controller, PAO sold $165,000 worth of shares at an average price of $33.00 on July 12th. The VP Corp Fin & Controller, PAO now owns $372,438 of the stock as reported to the SEC. Sean M. Lannon, VP Corp Fin & Controller, PAO let go of $165,000 worth of shares at an average price of $33.00 on Fri the 2nd. That brings Lannon’s holdings to $372,438 per an SEC filing yesterday.
 Charles W. Shaver, CEO disclosed the sale of 179,487 shares of AXTA stock. The shares were sold on May 15th for an average price of $31.32. The CEO now owns $16,565,367 of the stock per the Form 4 SEC filing.
 The following firms have also recently changed their position in AXTA.   As of the end of the quarter Seabridge Investment Advisors LLC had acquired 2,375 shares growing its stake by 2.4%. The value of the company’s investment in Axalta Coating Systems Ltd. went from $3,182,000 to $3,242,000 increasing 1.9% for the reporting period. As of quarter end Hermes Investment Management Ltd had sold  a total of 55,616 shares trimming its holdings by 6.0%. The value of the total investment in Axalta Coating Systems Ltd. decreased from $29,788,000 to $27,858,000 a change of 6.5% quarter to quarter.





 As of the end of the quarter Exane Asset Management had disposed of 57,995 shares trimming its position 17.7%. The value in dollars decreased from $10,560,000 to $8,649,000 a change of $1,911,000 quarter over quarter. As of quarter end Aperio Group, LLC had acquired 10,574 shares growing its holdings by 48.8%. The value of the investment in Axalta Coating Systems Ltd. increased from $698,000 to $1,034,000 a change of $336,000 since the last quarter.
  On July 18 analysts at Susquehanna initiated coverage on AXTA by announcing an initial rating of “Underperform”. On June 21 the company was downgraded to “Underperform” from “” in a statement from Bank of America.
 Gabelli & Co. started covering AXTA setting a rating of “Buy”. On July 27 the stock rating was upgraded from “Accumulate” to “Buy” by Seaport Global.
 On April 18 Citigroup kept the stock rating at “Buy” but moved up the price target from $32.00 to $36.00. On February 16 the company was upgraded from “Hold” to “Buy” in an announcement from Jefferies.
 The company is now down by -1.02% since yesterday’s close of $32.5.  It is currently trading at $32.17 which is a tad under the 50 day moving average which is $32.85 and a tad above the 200 day moving average of $31.02.  The 50 day moving average moved down $-0.68 and the 200 day average was up $1.15. 
 Axalta Coating Systems Ltd.’s P/E ratio is 106.52 and the market cap of the company is 7.79B.  In the last earnings report the EPS was $0.30 and is expected to be $1.40 for the current year with 242,100,000 shares outstanding.  Analysts expect next quarter’s EPS to be $0.39 with next year’s EPS anticipated to be $1.67. 
 Axalta Coating Systems Ltd. (Axalta), launched on August 24, 2012, is a holding company. The Company is a manufacturer, marketer and distributor of coatings systems primarily serving the transportation industry. The Business’s segments include Performance Coatings and Transportation Coatings. Through its Performance Coatings segment, the Company provides liquid and powder coatings solutions to a fragmented and local customer base. Through its Transportation Coatings segment, the Company provides coating technologies to original equipment manufacturers (OEMs) of light and commercial vehicles..






